instrumentqa

Class StationSOH

  • java.lang.Object
    • instrumentqa.StationSOH
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.xml.sax.ContentHandler

    public class StationSOH
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.xml.sax.ContentHandler
    Object class for storing information in StationSOH reports which are contained within iqxml messages from ASL. Each StationSOH report corresponds to a particular seismometer that should be considered out of service because of an "issue". The point of this class is to temporarily store information about a specific issue so that it can be compared to live records on an SQL table. This class utilizes a SAX xml parser.

        public StationSOH(int iqxmlid,
                  java.lang.String inxml,
                  java.lang.StringBuilder excps)
        Primary constructor for StationSOH objects. It stores the id of the iqxml report where the stationsoh report comes from and the xml information for a single stationsoh report.
        Parameters:
        iqxmlid - ID of the iqxmlid report the stationsoh comes from.
        inxml - Block of xml that contains stationsoh report information.
        excps - Used to collect exceptions generated in execution for email report.
